summary.text:
An Article is a kind of rich text document. Is specifically
a markdown document right now.
Add some markdown content as an Article.

The ComponentsAPI allows you to insert new MDX components
to be rendered into pages.

The CoreAPI is a list of API objects that contain
data and functions that handle specific features.

Each key lists a sub-api. This object is typically
merged with a PluginAPI object to form the DocApp

The DocApp type represents a collection of data that describes a
documentation website. It collects things such as:

- Routing
 - Demo Components
 - Markdown Articles
 - Reference Lookups
 - Custom Display Components

You can create a new instance of this object by called the

Every plugin included in a DocApp can create an API object, which is
attached to the PluginAPI object on via it's "key" property.

A "Reference" is a linkable piece of content
identifiable by some key. For instance, you might
want to build a canonical reference for a set of
typescript types, so you might build a set of
references that follow the following format:

  key = "@lkaalim/mypackage:MyExportedType.Property"

The RoutesAPI is a system to organize the visitable pages
for your application.
An array of plugins that can extend functionality
Get an instance of the DocApp used in the application.

content.text:
The context-shared DocApp instance used across the application. If required plugins
were provided, the plugin types are added to the return interface.

summary.text:
A list of plugins that this DocApp instance _requires_
for this hook to function. A runtime check is performed on the context-provided
DocApp instance to validate that the requested plugins are actually present (via their Key property).

readme.text:
_really_ barebones documentation component library for [@lukekaalim/act](https://act.luke.kaal.im).

Write some markdown, annotate with components, and bundle with
your tool of choice!
